---
description: System-design conventions for this scalable-starter-based project
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the full engineering conventions in `AGENTS.md` at the repo root. Core rules:

- **Layered architecture:** transport (routes) → service → repository → data.
  Routers stay thin; business logic goes in services; SQL lives only in
  repositories (never import FastAPI there).
- **Stateless compute:** no durable in-process state — all state in Postgres/Redis.
  Scale horizontally. Heavy/bursty work → the worker tier via `enqueue()` (handlers
  must be idempotent). Hot reads → read replica (`get_read_session`) + `get_or_set`
  cache-aside.
- **Config via `settings`** only (never `os.environ`); **schema via Alembic**
  migrations (never `create_all`, and name CheckConstraints).
- Errors as an `AppError` subclass → RFC-9457; outbound HTTP via the shared
  `HttpClient`; structured logs via `get_logger()` (never `print()`).
- **Add a resource** with `make feature name=<singular>`, then wire
  deps/model/router, then `make migration` + `make contract`. Frontend types are
  generated from OpenAPI — run `make contract`, never hand-edit `generated.ts`.
- `make check` must be green before committing.
